  "commentary": "With SPX at 6816 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6810 (-71.6B) and the positive gamma ceiling at 6830 (+26.3B), dealers are caught in aggressive hedging mode - buying the dip toward 6810 and selling any push toward 6830. The -26% GEX surge confirms dealers just got heavily short gamma, meaning they'll amplify any directional move that breaks out of this tight 6810-6830 range. Watch for explosive moves if we clear 6830 (dealers forced to chase higher) or break 6810 (dealers accelerate selling into the 6800-6805 negative gamma cluster).\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings between 6810-6830 until one side breaks.",
